            </figure>
          </sidebyside>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            The graph in <xref ref="functions-yes-or-no-function-1"/> is a function, because every input has only one output; however, the graph in <xref ref="functions-yes-or-no-function-2"/> is <em>not</em> a function because all inputs in <m>[-2,2]</m>
          </p>
        </solution>
      </example>

